'''''Peter Pan Live!''''' is a [[television special]] that was broadcast by [[NBC]] on December 4, 2014. The special featured a [[Live television|live]] production of the [[Peter Pan (1954 musical)|1954 musical adaptation]] of ''[[Peter and Wendy|Peter Pan]]'', televised from [[Grumman Studios]] in [[Bethpage, New York]], starring [[Allison Williams (actress)|Allison Williams]] in the [[Peter Pan|title role]] and [[Christopher Walken]] as [[Captain Hook]].

The production was a follow-up to ''[[The Sound of Music Live!]]''—a similar adaptation of ''[[The Sound of Music]]'' which aired on NBC in December 2013 and brought the network's highest Thursday-night ratings since 2004. NBC's entertainment head [[Bob Greenblatt]] would sign [[Craig Zadan]] and [[Neil Meron]]—who served as the [[executive producer]]s of the special, to produce another live musical for the 2014 holiday season. Additionally, the production served as a follow-up to three productions of ''Peter Pan'' produced for NBC in 1955, 1956, and 1960 that featured cast members from its original [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] run.  While similar in content to the original, the version of ''Peter Pan'' featured in the special contained revisions to its [[Book (musical theater)|book]] to emphasize the character of Captain Hook, along with additional songs from its revivals, new songs adapted from the musicals ''[[Do Re Mi (musical)|Do Re Mi]]'' and ''[[Say, Darling]]'', and the restoration of a song that had been cut from the musical before its original Broadway premiere.

