==Reception==
''Peter Pan Live!'' aired on the night of December 4, 2014 on NBC and was met with immediate public and critical reactions, both positive and negative. After a mediocre reception to the network's ''The Sound of Music Live!'' from 2013, many viewers were wary of the new production. Lead actress Allison Williams warned viewers in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'': “I will say this about last year: today’s audiences like to watch things cynically. And I’m on a show that’s cynical in tone so I’m no stranger to that … Hate-watching is a thing. It’s a whole way of watching something, and it’s not an audience that’s natural to a non-cynical performance. ''Peter Pan'', you cannot watch cynically. If you do, you’re going to hate it, no question. It falls apart instantly.”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/12/03/allison-williams-hate-watch-peter-pan/|title=Allison Williams says you cannot hate-watch 'Peter Pan Live'|first=James|last=Hibberd|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=2014-12-03| accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref> She said almost the opposite to [[NPR]], which reported that NBC expected that "hate-watchers" would help the event to succeed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/12/04/368308833/hate-the-idea-of-peter-pan-live-nbc-is-counting-on-it|title=Hate The Idea Of 'Peter Pan Live'? NBC Is Counting On It|first=Eric|last=Deggans|work=NPR|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref> Viewers shared their opinions on social media platforms using the hashtag #PeterPanLive and on the live blog on ''The Guardian'''s website, which gave such notes as: "As long and draggy and nonsensical as the show was, NBC didn’t spare any expense with the talent or production and they really pulled it off."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/tvandradioblog/live/2014/dec/04/peter-pan-live-liveblog|title=Peter Pan Live! - as it happened|first=Brian|last=Moylan|work=The Guardian|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/12/05/peter-pan-live-grows-121-versus-nbcs-non-sports-thursday-season-average/335772/|title='Peter Pan Live!' Grows 121% Versus NBC's Non-sports Thursday Season Average|date=December 5, 2014|accessdate=December 5, 2014|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers}}</ref>

While many reviewers expressed relief that the broadcast did not experience any major problems, critical reviews were mixed overall.<ref name="playbill-reviews">Hetrick, Adam. [https://www.playbill.com/news/article/the-verdict-read-reviews-of-peter-pan-live-on-nbc-336702 "The Verdict: Read Reviews of ''Peter Pan Live!'' on NBC"], ''Playbill'', December 4, 2014</ref> ''[[The New Yorker]]'' panned the broadcast, especially Williams and Walken.<ref>Larson, Sarah. [http://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/peter-pan-live-night-protests "''Peter Pan Live!'' and a Night of Protests"], ''[[The New Yorker]]'', December 5, 2014</ref> The [[Associated Press]] called the production "an oddly ponderous, disconnected, disjointed and jerky mess. If it had been a Broadway show, it would have gotten the hook (pun intended)."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/tv-review-nbcs-peter-pan-falls-sadly-flat-27381827|title=TV Review: NBC's 'Peter Pan' Falls Sadly Flat|first=Mark|last=Kennedy|work=Associated Press|publisher=ABC News|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref> The ''[[New York Daily News]]'' gave it two of five stars, writing that "we just weren't feeling the pixie dust".<ref>Hinckley, David. [http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/peter-pan-live-musical-fails-flight-review-article-1.2034154 "''Peter Pan Live!'' review: NBC musical starring Allison Williams, Christopher Walken fails to take flight"], ''New York Daily News'', December 5, 2014</ref> Likewise, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' called it "a woefully lifeless production".<ref>Lowry, Brian. [https://variety.com/2014/tv/reviews/tv-review-peter-pan-live-1201369373/ "TV Review: ''Peter Pan Live!''"], ''Variety'', December 5, 2014</ref>

''[[The A.V. Club]]'''s Caroline Siede gave the production a B+, calling it superior to the previous year's performance and a "colorful, competent, occasionally moving piece of musical theater", but assessing Williams as less strong a singer than Underwood.<ref name="avc">{{Cite web |url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/peter-pan-live-212645 |title=''Peter Pan Live!'' |publisher=[[The A.V. Club]] |last=Siede |first=Caroline |date=December 4, 2014}}</ref> ''[[USA Today]]'' gave it a mostly positive review for the production, but questioned the new material.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2014/12/04/peter-pan-live-nbc-review-robert-bianco/19922625/|title='Peter' not panned in NBC's live broadcast|first=Robert|last=Bianco|work=USA Today|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref> Melissa Maerz of ''Entertainment Weekly'' also gave it a mixed review calling it "Totally fine. ... Nothing spectacular. But nothing so embarrassing as NBC’s live production of ''The Sound of Music''".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/12/04/peter-pan-live-review/|title='Peter Pan Live' review: So was it really as bad as you'd hoped?|first=Melissa|last=Maerz|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' gave the production a rave review, highlighting both Williams' and Walken's performances saying, "It was a night where everything else about the play was shunted to the side as Williams and Walken grabbed your attention. Everything that could go wrong ''didn't'' go wrong and that's a credit the myriad people behind the scenes who pulled it off."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/peter-pan-live-tv-review-754093|title='Peter Pan Live!': TV Review|first=Tim|last=Goodman|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2014-12-04|accessdate=2014-12-05}}</ref>

=== Viewership ===
''Peter Pan Live!'' was seen in its original airing by 9.21 million viewers with a ratings share of 2.4/7 among adults 18–49, making it the most-watched program of the night across the major networks—but trailing a ''[[Thursday Night Football]]'' game on [[NFL Network]], which brought 9.1 million viewers, but had a larger 18–49 share of 3.2/10. The special also brought NBC its second-highest 18–49 ratings on Thursday night entertainment programming since ''The Sound of Music Live!'' before being surpassed by ''[[The Wiz Live!]]'' a year later. Greenblatt did not expect viewership for ''Peter Pan Live!'' to be as high as that of ''The Sound of Music Live!'', but still felt that NBC had a "great night", and thanked the cast and crew for their involvement in "three months of the hardest work I’ve ever seen."<ref name=variety-peterpanratings>{{cite web|title=‘Peter Pan Live’ Ratings: Not ‘Sound of Music’ Big But Strong for NBC Thursday|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/peter-pan-live-ratings-not-sound-of-music-big-but-strong-for-nbc-thursday-1201371871/|website=Variety|accessdate=5 December 2014}}</ref> [[Nielsen Online|Nielsen]] also estimated that over 475,000 posts were made about the telecast on [[Twitter]], which were seen 106.9 million times—more than double the number of views that tweets during ''The Sound of Music Live!'' received.<ref name=variety-peterpanratings/> The special retained 61% of its viewership, from beginning to end.<ref>Patten, Dominic (December 5, 2014). [http://deadline.com/2014/12/peter-pan-live-ratings-nbc-allison-williams-sound-of-music-1201310634/ ‘Peter Pan Live!’ Ratings Down 47% From ‘Sound Of Music’ Last Year, ‘The Taste’ Debuts Down – Update]. ''Deadline.com''. Retrieved December 8, 2014.</ref>

A behind-the-scenes special, ''The Making of Peter Pan Live!'', was broadcast by NBC on November 26, 2014<ref name="playbill-behind">Hetrick, Adam. [http://www.playbill.com/news/article/minnie-driver-will-fly-to-nbcs-peter-pan-live-making-of-special-sets-air-date-334818 "Minnie Driver Will Fly to NBC's ''Peter Pan Live!''; ''Making Of'' Special Sets Air Date"] Playbill.com, November 5, 2014. Accessed December 5, 2014.</ref> and seen by 3.02 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/12/01/wednesday-final-ratings-a-charlie-brown-thanksgiving-rebroadcast-adjusted-up/333903/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: 'A Charlie Brown Thanksgiving' Rebroadcast Adjusted Up|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=December 1, 2014|accessdate=December 1, 2014}}</ref> NBC showed an encore presentation of ''Peter Pan Live!'' on Saturday, December 13, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/PETER-PAN-LIVE-Flies-Again-Set-To-Re-Air-On-1213-20141212|title=PETER PAN LIVE! Flies Again Tonight On NBC|last=Cerasaro|first=Pat|work=Broadway World|date=December 13, 2014|accessdate=January 3, 2015}}</ref> The rebroadcast was seen by 1.5 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/12/14/tv-ratings-saturday-rudolph-the-red-nosed-reindeer-outshines-ufc-on-fox-48-hours-beats-2020/|title=TV Ratings Saturday: ‘Rudolph The Red Nosed Reindeer’ Outshines ‘UFC on FOX’, ’48 Hours’ Beats ’20/20′|work=TV By the Numbers|date=December 14, 2014|accessdate=December 6, 2015}}</ref>

==Home media release==
A [[DVD]] of the special was released on December 16, 2014,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/PETER-PAN-LIVE-DVD-Now-Available-For-Pre-Order-Out-1216-20141215|title= PETER PAN LIVE! DVD Now Available to Order|accessdate=June 5, 2015|work=Broadway World|publisher=Wisdom Digital Media|author=BWW News Desk|date=December 15, 2014}}</ref> through [[Universal Studios Home Entertainment]]. The DVD includes the behind-the-scenes special, ''The Making of Peter Pan Live!''.

